dependencies did not match the manually specified dependencies, which could cause the value to change more or less frequently than expected. The inferred dependency was `checkBoxListState`, but the source dependencies were [checkBoxStateList]. Inferred different dependency than source.\n\n/Users/minhyee/git/proxy/src/components/common/CheckBox.tsx:37:32\n  35 |   const isChecked = value !== undefined && checkBoxStateList[value];\n  36 |\n> 37 |   const isAllChecked = useMemo(() => hasInitState && checkBoxListState.every((state) => state), [checkBoxStateList]);\n     |                                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Could not preserve existing manual memoization\n  38 |   const isAnyChecked = useMemo(() => checkBoxListState.some((state) => state), [checkBoxStateList]) && isAllCheckBox;\n  39 |\n  40 |   const updateTotalCheckBoxState = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => {","ArrowFunctionExpression","Replace `left-0·top` with `top-0·left`",{"range":"1203","text":"1204"},"react-hooks/set-state-in-effect","Error: Calling setState synchronously within an effect can trigger cascading renders\n\nEffects are intended to synchronize state between React and external systems such as manually updating the DOM, state management libraries, or other platform APIs. In general, the body of an effect should do one or both of the following:\n* Update external systems with the latest state from React.\n* Subscribe for updates from some external system, calling setState in a callback function when external state changes.\n\nCalling setState synchronously within an effect body causes cascading renders that can hurt performance, and is not recommended. (https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect).\n\n/Users/minhyee/git/proxy/src/components/common/ModalPortal.tsx:12:5\n  10 |\n  11 |   useEffect(() => {\n> 12 |     setElement(document.getElementById(\"modal\"));\n     |     ^^^^^^^^^^ Avoid calling setState() directly within an effect\n  13 |   }, []);\n  14 |\n  15 |   return element ? createPortal(props.children, element) : null;","'props' is defined but never used. Allowed unused args must match /^_/u.","'useEffect' is defined but never used.",["1205"],["1206"],"'ProjectCard' is defined but never used.",["1207"],"'setIsLoading' is assigned a value but never used.",["1208"],"@typescript-eslint/triple-slash-reference","Do not use a triple slash reference for ./vite-env.d.ts, use `import` style instead.","Line","tripleSlashReference","Replace `'@electron-toolkit/preload'` with `\"@electron-toolkit/preload\";`",{"range":"1209","text":"1210"},{"range":"1211","text":"1017"},{"range":"1212","text":"1017"},"Replace `'electron'` with `\"electron\";`",{"range":"1213","text":"1214"},{"range":"1215","text":"1210"},{"range":"1216","text":"1017"},"Replace `'electron',·electronAPI)` with `\"electron\",·electronAPI);`",{"range":"1217","text":"1218"},"Replace `'api',·api)` with `\"api\",·api);`",{"range":"1219","text":"1220"},{"range":"1221","text":"1017"},{"range":"1222","text":"1017"},{"range":"1223","text":"1017"},{"range":"1224","text":"1160"},"Replace `'../../app/layout'` with `\"../../app/layout\";`",{"range":"1225","text":"1226"},"Replace `'../../app/page'` with `\"../../app/page\";`",{"range":"1227","text":"1228"},"Replace `'../../app/design-system/page'` with `\"../../app/design-system/page\";`",{"range":"1229","text":"1230"},"Replace `'../../app/licenses/page'` with `\"../../app/licenses/page\";`",{"range":"1231","text":"1232"},"Replace `'../../app/project/page'` with `\"../../app/project/page\";`",{"range":"1233","text":"1234"},"Replace `'undefined'·&&·window.location?.protocol·===·'file:'` with `\"undefined\"·&&·window.location?.protocol·===·\"file:\";`",{"range":"1235","text":"1236"},"Replace `'').trim()` with `\"\").trim();`",{"range":"1237","text":"1238"},"Replace `'home'` with `\"home\";`",{"range":"1239","text":"1240"},{"range":"1241","text":"1017"},{"range":"1242","text":"1240"},{